<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[87587]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Images of flight]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[An exhibition on at CaixaForum features photos taken by Brian Sokol, portraits of refugees from around the world.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The last two years has seen over three and a half million people from four countries in emergency situations (Syria, South Sudan, the Central African Republic and Mali) forced to flee from their countries.</p>
<p>Now an exhibition, organised in collaboration with the United Nations Refugee Agency (UNHCR), featuring photos taken by Sokol, who made a series of large-format portraits of refugees, showing the most important items they carried from the homes as they fled.</p>
